(1, 'Okonjo-Iweala didn’t save for the rainy day —Oshiomhole', '', NULL, 'EDO State governor  Comrade Adams Oshiomhole  has chided the immediate past Minister of Finance and Coordinating Minister of the Economy  Dr Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala  saying she did not save for the rainy day  According to Oshiomhole  if Nigerians said the governors were extravagant in spending and did not save for austere times  what about the minister who was in charge of over 50 per cent of oil produce ', 'EDO State governor  Comrade Adams Oshiomhole  has chided the immediate past Minister of Finance and Coordinating Minister of the Economy  Dr Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala  saying she did not save for the rainy day  According to Oshiomhole  if Nigerians said the governors were extravagant in spending and did not save for austere times  what about the minister who was in charge of over 50 per cent of oil produce ', 'http://tribuneonlineng.com/content/okonjo-iweala-didn%E2%80%99t-save-rainy-day-%E2%80%94oshiomhole', 1, 1, 1, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-06-23 10:20:25', '2015-06-23 10:20:25'),
(2, 'Fayose denies paying self N720m allowances', '', NULL, 'Ekiti State governor  Mr Ayo Fayose  has denied paying himself N720 million as terminal benefit for his first term tenure as alleged by the opposition All Progressives Congress  APC  in the state  Governor Fayose  who addressed the people of the state via the radio and television in a state-wide broadcast  said it would be    heartless of him    or any leaders for that matter to take such steps  considering the economic situation in the country ', 'Ekiti State governor  Mr Ayo Fayose  has denied paying himself N720 million as terminal benefit for his first term tenure as alleged by the opposition All Progressives Congress  APC  in the state  Governor Fayose  who addressed the people of the state via the radio and television in a state-wide broadcast  said it would be    heartless of him    or any leaders for that matter to take such steps  considering the economic situation in the country ', 'http://tribuneonlineng.com/content/fayose-denies-paying-self-n720m-allowances', 1, 1, 1, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-06-23 10:20:25', '2015-06-23 10:20:25'),
(3, 'NASS positions: APC supporters in Oyo angry', '', NULL, 'IF feelers from the National Assembly in Abuja is anything to go by  then some supporters of the All Progressives Congress  APC  members at the National Assembly are currently protesting the scheming which  according to them  is not favourable to members from the state  Sources informed the Nigerian Tribune that lawmakers from the state had been schemed out of power sharing formula  both at the red and green chambers  The development  it was gathered  had become a major concern to the supporters of the lawmakers ', 'IF feelers from the National Assembly in Abuja is anything to go by  then some supporters of the All Progressives Congress  APC  members at the National Assembly are currently protesting the scheming which  according to them  is not favourable to members from the state  Sources informed the Nigerian Tribune that lawmakers from the state had been schemed out of power sharing formula  both at the red and green chambers  The development  it was gathered  had become a major concern to the supporters of the lawmakers ', 'http://tribuneonlineng.com/content/nass-positions-apc-supporters-oyo-angry', 1, 1, 1, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-06-23 10:20:25', '2015-06-23 10:20:25'),
(4, 'Melaye joins Audu, 19 others in Kogi guber race', '', NULL, 'AHEAD the governorship election holding later this year in Kogi State  the senator representing Kogi West senatorial district  Dino Melaye  may have perfected plans to join the race to become the next governor of the state  after the incumbent  Captain Idris Wada  Melaye of All Progressives Congress  APC   who is yet to announce his ambition publicly  according to findings  would be joining about 20 other contenders  including the state APC leader and former governor  Prince Abubakar Audu ', 'AHEAD the governorship election holding later this year in Kogi State  the senator representing Kogi West senatorial district  Dino Melaye  may have perfected plans to join the race to become the next governor of the state  after the incumbent  Captain Idris Wada  Melaye of All Progressives Congress  APC   who is yet to announce his ambition publicly  according to findings  would be joining about 20 other contenders  including the state APC leader and former governor  Prince Abubakar Audu ', 'http://tribuneonlineng.com/content/melaye-joins-audu-19-others-kogi-guber-race', 1, 1, 1, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-06-23 10:20:26', '2015-06-23 10:20:26'),
(5, 'Ilemobade, ex-FUTA VC, abducted', '', NULL, 'A former Vice Chancellor of the Federal University of Technology  Akure  FUTA   Professor Albert Adeoye Ilemobade  was  on Monday morning  abducted by men suspected to be kidnappers at his residence  The former university don was reportedly abducted along with his gateman and was taken to an unknown destination  According to a close family source  his wife woke up in the morning and discovered he was not in the house  She also   discovered that the car was not in the compound and the gateman was also nowhere to be found ', 'A former Vice Chancellor of the Federal University of Technology  Akure  FUTA   Professor Albert Adeoye Ilemobade  was  on Monday morning  abducted by men suspected to be kidnappers at his residence  The former university don was reportedly abducted along with his gateman and was taken to an unknown destination  According to a close family source  his wife woke up in the morning and discovered he was not in the house  She also   discovered that the car was not in the compound and the gateman was also nowhere to be found ', 'http://tribuneonlineng.com/content/ilemobade-ex-futa-vc-abducted', 1, 1, 1, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-06-23 10:20:26', '2015-06-23 10:20:26'),
(6, 'Lagos lawyer drags Buhari to court over ministerial appointment', '', NULL, 'A Lagos-based lawyer  Ebun-Olu Adegboruwa  has approached a Federal High Court in Lagos with a suit seeking an order compelling President Muhammadu Buhari to appoint ministers or cease to be president of the Federal Republic of Nigeria  In the suit filed on Monday  the human rights lawyer said the continued stay of action of President Buhari on the appointment of his ministers was contrary to the constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria ', 'A Lagos-based lawyer  Ebun-Olu Adegboruwa  has approached a Federal High Court in Lagos with a suit seeking an order compelling President Muhammadu Buhari to appoint ministers or cease to be president of the Federal Republic of Nigeria  In the suit filed on Monday  the human rights lawyer said the continued stay of action of President Buhari on the appointment of his ministers was contrary to the constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria ', 'http://tribuneonlineng.com/content/lagos-lawyer-drags-buhari-court-over-ministerial-appointment', 1, 1, 1, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-06-23 10:20:26', '2015-06-23 10:20:26'),
